@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{elpaca-extras.el} extends the @samp{elpaca} package manager with commands that make it easier to iterate on packages without restarting Emacs. When you update or rebuild a package, its old definitions remain loaded in the running session. These extensions automate the tedious process of unloading stale features and reloading the updated versions, and they also provide filtered lock-file writing.

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Reload after update.} A command that updates a package and automatically reloads its features once the build finishes (@ref{Update and reload}).
@item
@strong{Reload after rebuild.} The same workflow for package rebuilds (@ref{Rebuild and reload}).
@item
@strong{Manual reload.} A standalone reload command for when you have made local edits to a package's source (@ref{Reload}).
@item
@strong{Filtered lock files.} Writing Elpaca lock files while excluding specific packages (@ref{Lock file management}).
@end itemize

@node User options
@chapter User options

