@node @code{elpaca-extras-write-lock-file-excluded}
@section @code{elpaca-extras-write-lock-file-excluded}

@vindex elpaca-extras-write-lock-file-excluded
The user option @code{elpaca-extras-write-lock-file-excluded} specifies a list of package identifiers (symbols) that should be omitted when writing a lock file with @code{elpaca-extras-write-lock-file-excluding} (@ref{Lock file management}). This is useful for packages that are installed from local sources or that you do not want pinned to a specific revision.

The default value is @code{nil} (no exclusions). The type is a list of symbols.

